# The authoritative environment template is the repo-root .env.example
# (single source of truth for the whole stack — bridge + orchestrator + RAG +
# booking). Do not maintain a divergent copy here.
#
# Dev: from the repo root, symlink it in so `make orch-dev` (which runs from
# orchestrator/) picks it up:
#
#     cp ../.env.example ../.env      # fill it in, once
#     ln -sf ../.env .env             # orchestrator reads ./.env via python-dotenv
#
# Prod: systemd loads /etc/skill-chatbot.env (EnvironmentFile); no file here.
#
# Every var the orchestrator reads — inference, Qdrant/RAG, Composio/booking,
# bridge I/O, notify, admin — is documented and grouped in the root template.
